Use `@MappedSuperclass`:   
```
@MappedSuperclass
public class BaseEntity {
    // here you can add common fields for your entities
}
```  
and then extend from it:  
```
@Entity
public class User extends BaseEntity {
    // user specific fields goes here
}
```   
and `Client`:   
```
@Entity
@Table(name = &quot;cliente&quot;)
public class Cliente extends BaseEntity {
    // client specific fields here
}
```   
For more info read [How to inherit properties from a base class entity using @MappedSuperclass with JPA and Hibernate](https://vladmihalcea.com/how-to-inherit-properties-from-a-base-class-entity-using-mappedsuperclass-with-jpa-and-hibernate/)

